Package: showMissings
Type: Package
Title: Create a heatmap depicting missing values in a data frame
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Mireia Ferrer and Alex Sanchez
Description: This function transforms a data.frame or tibble into a data frame whose content is 1 if the value is not an NA or 0 in case it is. Additionally the rows are sorted according the order defined by "rowGroups" levels, set by "varLabels" Also columns are sorted by order defined by  by "varNames" "varGroups" and "varLabels" are only used to define variable groups and names to be used in heatmap.
Imports: pheatmap, dplyr, magrittr
License: GPL 2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
